Map: I would like to show stream status in Ottawa County, Michigan using stream status data, streams/river vector data, and counties vector data as bounding box. The large data sets (NLCD_2024_CU.tif and Assessment_Units_2024_-_Rivers_and_Streams.geojson) need to downloaded from email.

Load libraries:

source("setup.R")
library(gifski)

Read in vector data: MI stream status and county data and check CRS match:

From the Michigan stream status Metadata: The Section 303(d) list includes Michigan water bodies that are not attaining one or more designated use and require the establishment of Total Maximum Daily Loads (TMDLs) to meet and maintain Water Quality Standards. It should be noted that these comprehensive datasets include assessment units throughout the state of Michigan and are not limited to those on the Section 303d list.

Water bodies are evaluated for the Total Body Contact (TBC) and Partial Body Contact (PBC) recreation using E. coli bacteria as an indicator for other harmful pathogens. (EGLE)

#Data from Michigan Dept. of Environment, Great Lakes, and Energy (EGLE).CRS in WGS 84/ EPSG 4326
streams <- st_read("data/Assessment_Units_2024_-_Rivers_and_Streams.geojson") 

#subset to only relevant cols
sub_streams<- streams %>%
  select(AUID,EPAIRCategory, EPA303dImpairment,
         TotalBodyContactAttainment, PartialBodyContactAttainment,FishConsumptionAttainment, geometry)
  
#Ottawa county data 2024
ott<-counties(state = "MI") %>% 
     filter(NAME == "Ottawa") 

# Ensure CRS match (they don't) 
st_crs(sub_streams) == st_crs(ott)
st_crs(sub_streams)

# transform the CRS of ott to the CRS of sub_streams (WGS84)
ott_prj <- st_transform(ott, st_crs(sub_streams))
st_crs(sub_streams) == st_crs(ott_prj)

Now download landcover raster data and crop to Ottawa county:

#read in the 2024 landcover raster using rast() function
landcover <- terra::rast("data/NLCD_2024_CU.tif")
class(landcover) #spat raster
crs(landcover)
crs(ott_prj)

#each grid cell can be linked to the land cover. file extension nlcd. landcover legend.

#convert ott_prj sf from polygon to raster and to raster CRS
ott_prj_vect <- vect(st_transform(ott_prj, crs(landcover)))

# Crop raster to county extent (fast)
landcover_crop <- crop(landcover, ott_prj_vect)
# Mask to polygon shape
landcover_clip <- mask(landcover_crop, ott_prj_vect)

# Reproject NLCD raster to match WGS 84
landcover_clip <- terra::project(landcover_clip, "EPSG:4326")

Because the NLCD auxillary files has some issues, we will filter to only a select number of land types and customize colors. Rebuild the NLCD class table (using your RAT)

NLCD class values and the RGB colors come directly from the official USGS NLCD metadata

nlcd <- data.frame(
  value = c(11,12,21,22,23,24,31,41,42,43,52,71,81,82,90,95),
  class = c(
    "Open Water","Perennial Ice/Snow",
    "Developed, Open Space","Developed, Low Intensity",
    "Developed, Medium Intensity","Developed, High Intensity",
    "Barren Land","Deciduous Forest","Evergreen Forest","Mixed Forest",
    "Shrub/Scrub","Grassland/Herbaceous",
    "Pasture/Hay","Cultivated Crops",
    "Woody Wetlands","Emergent Herbaceous Wetlands"
  ),
  R = c(70,209,222,217,235,171,179,104,28,181,204,223,220,171,184,108),
  G = c(107,222,197,146,0,0,172,171,95,197,184,223,217,108,217,159),
  B = c(159,248,197,130,0,0,159,95,44,143,121,194,57,40,235,184)
)

# convert to hex colors
nlcd$hex <- rgb(nlcd$R, nlcd$G, nlcd$B, maxColorValue = 255)

keep <- c(11, 24, 22, 41, 42, 43, 90, 95, 82, 31, 81)

#Create the filtered raster (1 object). Everything not in keep is turned to NA.
landcover_small <- terra::classify(
  landcover_clip,
  cbind(nlcd$value, ifelse(nlcd$value %in% keep, nlcd$value, NA)))

# attach labels only for the kept classes and check map
sel <- nlcd[nlcd$value %in% keep, ]
tm_shape(landcover_small) +
  tm_raster(
    style = "cat",
    palette = sel$hex,
    labels  = sel$class,
    title   = "Selected NLCD Landcover",
    drop.levels = TRUE,   # hides unused categories
    legend.show = TRUE
  )

Filter Streams to Ottawa County and classify impairment for mapping:

# Clip streams to Ottawa County boundaries
ott_streams <- st_intersection(sub_streams, ott_prj)

#classify
ott_streams<- ott_streams %>%
  filter(!is.na(EPA303dImpairment)) %>%
  mutate(s_status= if_else(`EPA303dImpairment` == 1,"Impaired","Not Impaired"))

# ensure s_status is a factor so it maps with no issues
ott_streams$s_status <- factor(ott_streams$s_status, levels = c("Impaired", "Not Impaired"))

Static map:

#set mode to plot or view for interactive
tmap_mode("plot")

#raster likes auxillary file to categorize. might be package

  # Final map
final_map<- tm_shape(landcover_small) +
  tm_raster(
    style = "cat",          # treat raster as categorical
    palette = sel$hex,      # colors for the selected classes
    labels  = sel$class,    # class names for legend
    title   = "NLCD Landcover"
  ) +
  tm_shape(ott_prj) +
  tm_borders(col = "black", lwd = 2) +
  tm_shape(ott_streams) +
  tm_lines(
    col = "s_status",
    palette = c("black", "blue"),
    title = "Stream Status",
    lwd = 0.5) +
  tm_layout(
    title = "Streams in Ottawa County, MI with Impairment Status",
    legend.outside = TRUE,
    legend.title.size = 1,
    legend.text.size = 0.8,
    frame = FALSE
  ) +
  tm_scalebar(position = c("left", "bottom")) +
  tm_compass(position = c("left", "top")) +
  tm_credits("Data sources: NLCD 2024, EGLE 2024", position = c("right", "bottom"))

#save map as PNG
tmap_save(final_map, "final_map.png", width = 10, height = 8, units = "in", dpi = 300)
